6. Relationships (Logical)
signal_raw_capture → signal (N:1)
signal → signal_provenance (1:N)
signal → signal_dedupe_ref (1:N)
signal → signal_decision (1:N)
signal → signal_aggregate (N:M via logic)
signal → signal_correlation_group (N:M)
7. Cross-Engine Data Contracts
Engine
References
PIE
signal_id, signal_type, scores
SIM
signal_id, aggregates
DAT
execution signal_id
FLO
financial signal_id
GGP
signal_decision
Signals are referenced by ID only.
8. Invariants & Constraints
signal rows are immutable
derived tables are disposable
every signal has at least one provenance link
all decisions are recorded
9. Document Position in SIG Corpus
This data model builds upon:
NS-SIG-002 — TAXONOMY
NS-SIG-003 — ARCHITECTURE
NS-SIG-006 — VERSION
It informs:
NS-SIG-008 — EEE
NS-SIG-013 — RUNBOOK
